A web and mobile [[EWallet]] used for sending, receiving and storing bitcoins.

The mobile and web clients are front ends to a hosted bitcoin wallet.

An API is available.

##History

The service was announced on April 5, 2012 (2.1).  The operator of Paytunia also operates [[Bitcoin-Central]] exchange and all exchange accounts are accessible through Paytunia's web and mobile wallet as well. 

